Q1. What flag do we use to specify a BSSID to attack?
Ans: -b

Q2. What flag do we use to specify a wordlist?
Ans: -w

Q3. How do we create a HCCAPX in order to use hashcat to crack the password?
Ans: -j

Q4. Using the rockyou wordlist, crack the password in the attached capture. What's the password?
[HINT]: Run the following command: 
    ''' sudo aircrack-ng test taskfilename.cap      (this command will convert the .cap file to the .hccapx format so that we can crack the password using aricrack-ng or hashcat) and then run the following command to get the passowrd:
    ''' sudo aircrack-ng -b <bssid> -w /usr/share/wordlist/rockyou.txt test  '''

Ans: greeneggsandham


Q5. Where is password cracking likely to be fastest, CPU or GPU?
Ans: GPU
